<li id="cite_note-Booth_letter-17"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Booth_letter_17-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Booth_letter_17-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Booth_letter_17-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Booth_letter_17-3"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text">Ezra Booth, letter dated December 6, 1831, <i>Ohio Star</i> (Ravenna, Ohio), December 8, 1831. Text at <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20110607042149/http://www.saintswithouthalos.com/p/1831_booth8-9.phtml#marry">Saints Without Halos</a>, archived from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.saintswithouthalos.com/p/1831_booth8-9.phtml">the original</a> on June 7th, 2011. Reprinted in <a href="#CITEREFHowe1834">Howe 1834</a>.</span>
