<li id="cite_note-1843_text-49"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1843_text_49-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The 1843 polygamy revelation was made public by Brigham Young on August 29, 1852, in the <a href="/wiki/Salt_Lake_Tabernacle" title="Salt Lake Tabernacle">Salt Lake Tabernacle</a> and was codified in the 1870s in the church's <a href="/wiki/Doctrine_and_Covenants" title="Doctrine and Covenants">Doctrine and Covenants</a> <a href="https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/The_Doctrine_and_Covenants/Section_132" class="extiw" title="s:The Doctrine and Covenants/Section 132">132:1â4, 19, 20, 24, 34, 35, 38, 39, 52, 60â66</a>.. See the <i><a href="/wiki/Doctrine_and_Covenants" title="Doctrine and Covenants">Doctrine and Covenants</a></i>, <a href="https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/The_Doctrine_and_Covenants/Section_132" class="extiw" title="s:The Doctrine and Covenants/Section 132">132:1â4, 19, 20, 24, 34, 35, 38, 39, 52, 60â66</a>.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-50"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-50">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">"[I]f she receive not this law ... she then becomes the transgressor; and he is exempt[.]" The final portion of <a href="https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/The_Doctrine_and_Covenants/Section_132" class="extiw" title="s:The Doctrine and Covenants/Section 132">D&amp;C 132:65</a> has been interpreted as meaning that the husband is exempt from asking for his wife's consent in the future.<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFCherniak2007" class="citation cs2">Cherniak, Cetti (2007), "The Theology of Desire", <i><a href="/wiki/Dialogue:_A_Journal_of_Mormon_Thought" title="Dialogue: A Journal of Mormon Thought">Dialogue: A Journal of Mormon Thought</a></i>, <b>40</b> (2), <a href="/wiki/Doi_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Doi (identifier)">doi</a>:<span class="id-lock-free" title="Freely accessible"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.5406%2Fdialjmormthou.40.2.0001">10.5406/dialjmormthou.40.2.0001</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/S2CID_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="S2CID (identifier)">S2CID</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://api.semanticscholar.org/CorpusID:246629178">246629178</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Dialogue%3A+A+Journal+of+Mormon+Thought&amp;rft.atitle=The+Theology+of+Desire&amp;rft.volume=40&amp;rft.issue=2&amp;rft.date=2007&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.5406%2Fdialjmormthou.40.2.0001&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fapi.semanticscholar.org%2FCorpusID%3A246629178%23id-name%3DS2CID&amp;rft.aulast=Cherniak&amp;rft.aufirst=Cetti&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AOrigin+of+Latter+Day+Saint+polygamy" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
