<li id="cite_note-69"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-69">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFRollins_Lightner1926" class="citation journal cs1">Rollins Lightner, Mary Elizabeth (July 1926). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.boap.org/LDS/Early-Saints/MLightner.html">"Autobiography of Mary E. Lightner"</a>. <i>The Utah Genealogical and Historical Magazine</i>. <b>17</b><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">December 12,</span> 2016</span>. <q>I knew he had three children. They told me. I think two are living today but they are not known as his children as they go by other names.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Utah+Genealogical+and+Historical+Magazine&amp;rft.atitle=Autobiography+of+Mary+E.+Lightner&amp;rft.volume=17&amp;rft.date=1926-07&amp;rft.aulast=Rollins+Lightner&amp;rft.aufirst=Mary+Elizabeth&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.boap.org%2FLDS%2FEarly-Saints%2FMLightner.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AOrigin+of+Latter+Day+Saint+polygamy" class="Z3988"></span></span>
